  • Real-World Analogies: Relate your work to something familiar to her. For instance, explain your narrative intelligence as storytelling, something everyone can connect with.

  • Emotional Resistance: The idea of engaging deeply with a new concept might feel daunting.

3. Engage Her Interests

4. Remove the Pressure

Sometimes, enthusiasm can come across as forceful, which might make her defensive. Shift the approach to:

  • Letting her discover things at her own pace.

  • Sharing a little and then backing off, letting her curiosity take over if she’s open to it.
